---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const pageTitle = "The Advanced Uses of “Would” in English – IELTS Corner";
const pageDescription =
  "A detailed lesson on the different uses of “would” in English, including conditionals, habits, politeness, and speculation.";
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-meta">C1 · Grammar</div>
      <h1 class="card-title">The Advanced Uses of “Would” in English</h1>
      <p class="text-muted">
        This is a placeholder layout for your flagship “would” lesson. We’ll plug in
        your full explanations, examples, and exercises next.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-4">
        <h2>What this lesson covers</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>• “Would” in conditionals (real vs unreal situations)</li>
          <li>• “Would” for past habits vs “used to”</li>
          <li>• “Would” for polite requests and offers</li>
          <li>• “Would” in reported speech and indirect questions</li>
          <li>• “Would” for speculation and imagined futures</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-4">
        <p>
          For now, this page just proves the layout and navigation work. The next step
          is to take your existing lesson plan and build it into sections with examples,
          short explanations, and practice tasks.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
